HEADWORD: Diffusivity
<hw>Dif`fu*siv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Tendency to
become diffused; tendency, as of heat, to become equalized by spreading
through a conducting medium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

